08/07/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The European Commission (EC) will approve a proposal removing Schengen visas for citizens of Macedonia, Montenegro and Serbia on July 14th, the press office of European Commissioner for Justice and Internal Affairs Jacques Barrot announced on Tuesday (July 7th). 
The proposal will then be forwarded to the EU Council of Ministers and the European Parliament for consideration. 
(B92, Tanjug, RTS, BTA - 07/07/09)
